This paper deals with data augmentation techniques for improving the performance of neural models in the task of dialog response selection. This task falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is covered by the cs.CL sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning models, which are covered by the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also deals with information retrieval, which is covered by the cs.IR sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of synthetic data, which is covered by the cs.SI sub-category.
